Introduction

KISS OF LIFE, also shortened as KIOF, is a four-member multinational South Korean girl group under S2 Entertainment. The group is composed of Julie, Natty, Belle, and Haneul. They made their official debut on July 5th, 2023, with their self-titled mini album "KISS OF LIFE".

On December 27, 2022, S2 Entertainment announced plans to debut a new girl group in the first half of the following year. The company described the group as comprising members with a combination of visual appeal, talent, and potential, aiming to showcase a unique charm distinct from existing girl groups.

On March 21, 2023, S2 Entertainment confirmed Natty as the first member of the upcoming girl group. The group's official social media accounts, under the name KISS OF LIFE, were launched on May 11. Belle was introduced as the second member on May 16, followed by Julie on May 17, and Haneul on May 18.

Prior to the release of their debut album, the group unveiled several pre-release tracks, including solo songs from the members and a b-side track. These releases highlighted the members' individual musicality and involvement in songwriting and production, with all members contributing as lyricists or producers.
